Place @roast veggie mix{1%packet} on a large #microwave-safe plate{}. Cover with a damp
#paper towel{}. Microwave veggies on high, ~{4%minutes}. Drain and transfer to a
#baking dish{}.

Meanwhile, roughly chop @zucchini{1} into bite-sized chunks.

To the baking dish with steamed veggies, add zucchini and drizzle with @olive oil{1%drizzle}.
Season with @salt{} and toss to coat. Roast until just tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

In a large #frying pan{}, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.

Cook @diced bacon{180%g} until golden, ~{4-6%minutes}. Add @herb & mushroom seasoning{1%sachet},
and the @flour{1%tsp} and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @milk{1%cup}, @water{2%tbs}, @light cooking cream{1%packet} and @Parmesan cheese{1%packet}
and cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season to taste with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Pour creamy filling over veggies in the baking dish.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, add the @butter{20%g}, then microwave in
~{10%second} bursts until melted.

Lightly scrunch each sheet of @filo pastry{1/2%packet} (3 sheets per person) and place
on top of pie filling to completely cover. Gently brush the melted butter over pastry
to coat.

Bake pie until golden, ~{15-20%minutes}.

In a medium #bowl{}, combine @rocket{1%packet} leaves with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%drizzle}
and @vinegar{1%drizzle}(balsamic or white wine). Season to taste.

Divide creamy bacon and veggie filo pie between plates. Serve with rocket. Enjoy!